Review comment:
       I do not think it is worthwhile, given that the optimized implementation consists of a pair of logical operations compared to [utf8proc_iterate](https://github.com/JuliaStrings/utf8proc/blob/master/utf8proc.c#L124-L171) which has several branches and a few other operations for validating continuation bytes. The rest of *utf8_length* implementation is basically the same for both variants, so the optimized version should be clearly faster.




